programme.sub-title: The origin of freeride mountain biking

In the backwoods of British Columbia, Canada three crews of adventure seekers were quietly changing the course of a sport and carving their paths in history. programme.title: The Hidden Colony
programme.desc: An international group of skateboarders hits the best urban skate spots Hong Kong has to offer. An international group of skateboarders hits the best urban skate spots Hong Kong has to offer, including an array of parks, back alleys, ditches and more.

programme.title: Where the river meets the ocean
programme.desc: A group of skateboarders head to Uruguay to see what the country has to offer and find the perfect skate spot. Led by Carlos Iqui, a group of skateboarders including Wes Kremer, Chris Pfanner, and Madars Apse, head to Uruguay to see what the country has to offer and discover the perfect skate vacation.

programme.title: Singapore
programme.desc: Ryan Decenzo and friends shred the nearly unbelievable skate spots of Singapore. Singapore’s nickname, The Marble City, should be enough to attract skateboarders all by itself. As Ryan Decenzo, Barney Page, and TJ Rogers discover when they hook up with local ripper Farris Rahman, this city is a skateboarder's utopia.

programme.title: Hooked on Belgian Metal
programme.sub-title: An inside look into Belgium's metal scene
programme.desc: Get to know the importance of the Belgian metal scene and how it has transformed metal music internationally. The Belgian metal music scene transgresses far beyond the country's national borders. From popular bands performing at international events back in the 1980s to the present day, get to know the importance of the Belgian metal genre.

programme.title: The deadline is looming
programme.desc: 'Mad' Mike Whiddett begins stripping down the Lamborghini in order to build it into a powerful ride. 'Mad' Mike Whiddett continues his mission to turn a Lamborghini into his dream car by stripping it down in order to build it into a powerful ride. The pressure is on as the deadline approaches.

programme.title: Testing the dream
programme.desc: The time has come for 'Mad' Mike Whiddett to finally drive his drift Lamborghini for the first time. The time has come for 'Mad' Mike Whiddett to finally drive his drift Lamborghini for the first time. After so much hard work and many late nights, how well will the car drive?

programme.title: Test driving before Goodwood
programme.desc: 'Mad' Mike Whiddett's Lamborghini Huracán is ready for its big reveal at the Goodwood Festival of Speed. 'Mad' Mike Whiddett's Lamborghini Huracán is finally ready for its big reveal at the Goodwood Festival of Speed, but first he's got to make sure it doesn't get flattened by Kamaz's huge Dakar truck.

programme.title: Follow Your Nose
programme.sub-title: Two powder hounds on the hunt for epic snow
programme.desc: Snowboarders Gigi Rüf and Elias Elhardt leave search of unshredded pow in the backcountry. Gigi Rüf and Elias Elhardt share a passion for exploring the unknown. The journey to find new lines is as much a part of the soul of snowboarding as the turns themselves. Together, they create high-velocity art in the deep snow of the backcountry.

programme.title: Blood on the Crack
programme.desc: Climbers Kevin Jorgeson and Jacob Cook take on one of the most excruciating crack climbs in the world. Kevin Jorgeson and Jacob Cook head to the Bugaboos to attempt the second ascent of the Tom Egan Memorial Route, which contains one of the hardest, most excruciating crack climbs in the world, renowned for reducing fingertips to shreds.

programme.title: Heli Runs and Shooting Guns
programme.desc: Jake and Roland are blessed with a perfect day for snowboarding... and shooting guns with locals. Snowboarders Jake Koia and Roland Morley-Brown gear up for another epic bluebird day in Alaska's backcountry. After shredding some huge, picturesque lines, they decide the best way to follow that up is to shoot some high-powered guns with the locals.

programme.title: Haines Lines and Crashes
programme.desc: Jake and Roland's excitement gets the best of them as they drop into some lines that end up being sketchy. Snowboarders Jake Koia and Roland Morely-Brown head out for another day of heli riding and learn a lesson in not forcing it. They drop into lines that turn out to be as dicey as they looked from the air, and no amount of hoping will change that.

programme.title: Disc Golf and Slam Dunks
programme.desc: The snowboarding mates spend a day meeting the wildlife, playing disc golf, and racing vintage snowmobiles. When the weather doesn't cooperate for snowboarding, it's time to find other distractions. Jake and Roland spend a down day hanging out with some wolves, playing disc golf, riding old snowmobiles, and having a good-old fashioned Alaskan bonfire.

programme.title: La Liste
programme.desc: Over the course two seasons, young phenom Jérémie Heitz tries to ski 15 of the steepest peaks in the Alps. Young skiing phenom Jérémie Heitz challenges himself to ski 15 steepest 4,000m peaks in the Alps in just two ski seasons. To do so requires enormous physical endurance and superior mental fortitude. This is a new frontier in freeriding.

programme.title: Melodies for the Lemurs
programme.desc: A group of skaters travel to beautiful Madagascar in search of new skate territory. A group of skaters travel to beautiful Madagascar in search of new skate territory. Along the way, they engage with locals: some who do anything to skate, and some who have never seen a board before.

programme.title: Progression
programme.desc: Olympic triathlete Courtney Atkinson and freerunner Ryan Doyle are on quests to push their sports forward. For elite athletes, it all adds up to either progression or stagnation. After two decades of dominance, Olympic triathlete Courtney Atkinson takes on the IRONMAN competition, while freerunner Ryan Doyle pushes himself to defy rules and limitations.

programme.title: Personal best
programme.desc: Hang glider Jon Durand and rock climber Sasha DiGiulia face their biggest competitors: themselves. Hang glider Jon Durand and rock climber Sasha DiGiulian may not have much in common on the surface, but they both understand that they can be their own strongest competitor. Each is on a quest to reach a new personal best.

programme.title: Hiroshima
programme.desc: An international group of BMX riders head to Japan to compete in the FISE World Series. An international group of BMX riders, including Daniel Dhers, Rim Nakamura, Marin Ranteš and Daniel Sandoval, head to Hiroshima, Japan, to compete in the FISE World Series.

programme.title: Montpellier
programme.desc: Follow Daniel Sandoval and Daniel Dhers as they battle to qualify for the Summer Olympics in Tokyo 2020. In the summer of 2020, BMX Freestyle will be on the biggest stage the sport has ever seen. Follow Daniel Sandoval and Daniel Dhers as they battle to qualify for the Summer Olympics in Tokyo.

programme.title: Two 2 Four Wheels
programme.sub-title: MotoGP™ and MXGP take on F1
programme.desc: See how Marc Márquez, Dani Pedrosa and Tony Cairoli get on behind the wheel of an F1 car. MotoGP™ champions Marc Márquez and Dani Pedrosa, and motocross champ Tony Cairoli, try out an F1 car in a simulator at Red Bull Racing HQ in the UK, then on the track at the Red Bull Ring in Austria.
